## 10. Technical Recommendations

### Database Schema (PostgreSQL + PostGIS)

```sql
-- Core tables
CREATE TABLE taxi_services (
  id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
  name VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,
  priority INT DEFAULT 0,
  settlement VARCHAR(100),
  auto_selection_type VARCHAR(50) -- 'nearest', 'priority', 'queue'
);

CREATE TABLE vehicle_class_groups (
  id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
  name VARCHAR(100) -- 'Легковые', 'Грузовые', or '' for hidden
);

CREATE TABLE vehicle_classes (
  id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
  group_id INT REFERENCES vehicle_class_groups(id),
  name VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL -- 'Эконом', 'Комфорт', 'VIP'...
);

CREATE TABLE tariffs (
  id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
  service_id INT REFERENCES taxi_services(id),
  class_id INT REFERENCES vehicle_classes(id),
  base_price NUMERIC(10,2) NOT NULL,
  price_per_km NUMERIC(10,4),
  price_per_min NUMERIC(10,4),
  min_price NUMERIC(10,2),
  free_wait_minutes INT DEFAULT 5,
  extra_wait_price NUMERIC(10,4)
);

CREATE EXTENSION IF NOT EXISTS postgis;

CREATE TABLE geozones (
  id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
  name VARCHAR(100),
  type VARCHAR(50), -- 'boundary', 'zone'
  polygon GEOMETRY(POLYGON, 4326) NOT NULL
);
CREATE INDEX geozones_geo_idx ON geozones USING GIST(polygon);

CREATE TABLE geozone_prices (
  id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
  tariff_id INT REFERENCES tariffs(id),
  geozone_from_id INT REFERENCES geozones(id),
  geozone_to_id INT REFERENCES geozones(id),
  price_override NUMERIC(10,2)
);

CREATE TABLE drivers (
  id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
  group_id INT,
  callsign VARCHAR(20),
  last_name VARCHAR(100),
  first_name VARCHAR(100),
  middle_name VARCHAR(100),
  phone VARCHAR(20) UNIQUE,
  login VARCHAR(50) UNIQUE,
  password_hash VARCHAR(255),
  tariff_group_id INT,
  max_credit NUMERIC(10,2) DEFAULT 0,
  status VARCHAR(20) DEFAULT 'offline', -- 'free', 'busy', 'offline'
  current_location GEOMETRY(POINT, 4326),
  device_id VARCHAR(100)
);
CREATE INDEX drivers_location_idx ON drivers USING GIST(current_location);

CREATE TABLE vehicles (
  id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
  plate VARCHAR(20) UNIQUE,
  make VARCHAR(100),
  model VARCHAR(100),
  color VARCHAR(50),
  ownership_type VARCHAR(20), -- 'driver', 'company'
  driver_id INT REFERENCES drivers(id)
);

CREATE TABLE orders (
  id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
  phone VARCHAR(20),
  client_id INT,
  service_id INT REFERENCES taxi_services(id),
  driver_id INT REFERENCES drivers(id),
  operator_id INT,
  vehicle_id INT,
  tariff_id INT REFERENCES tariffs(id),
  pickup_address TEXT,
  pickup_point GEOMETRY(POINT, 4326),
  dropoff_address TEXT,
  dropoff_point GEOMETRY(POINT, 4326),
  stops JSONB DEFAULT '[]',
  distance_km NUMERIC(10,3),
  class_id INT REFERENCES vehicle_classes(id),
  price NUMERIC(10,2),
  cashless_account_id INT,
  use_bonuses BOOLEAN DEFAULT FALSE,
  distribution_method VARCHAR(50), -- 'auto', 'broadcast', 'sequential', 'map', 'list'
  status VARCHAR(30) DEFAULT 'pending', -- 'pending','assigned','arrived','in_progress','completed','canceled'
  comment TEXT,
  print_receipt BOOLEAN DEFAULT FALSE,
  scheduled_at TIMESTAMPTZ,
  created_at TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT NOW(),
  assigned_at TIMESTAMPTZ,
  arrived_at TIMESTAMPTZ,
  started_at TIMESTAMPTZ,
  completed_at TIMESTAMPTZ
);

CREATE TABLE call_logs (
  id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
  timestamp TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT NOW(),
  phone_from VARCHAR(20),
  phone_to VARCHAR(20),
  call_type VARCHAR(20), -- 'inbound', 'outbound'
  operator_id INT,
  service_id INT REFERENCES taxi_services(id),
  duration_total_sec INT,
  duration_wait_sec INT,
  duration_talk_sec INT,
  status VARCHAR(30) -- 'answered', 'missed', 'busy'
);

CREATE TABLE cash_transactions (
  id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
  operator_id INT NOT NULL,
  transaction_type VARCHAR(20), -- 'payout', 'deposit'
  amount NUMERIC(10,2),
  timestamp TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT NOW(),
  linked_order_id INT REFERENCES orders(id)
);
```

### API Endpoints

| Method | Endpoint | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `POST` | `/api/auth/login` | Login for operators |
| `POST` | `/api/auth/driver/login` | Login for drivers (mobile app) |
| `POST` | `/api/orders` | Create a new order |
| `GET` | `/api/orders` | List orders (with filters: status, date, driver, service) |
| `GET` | `/api/orders/:id` | Get single order details |
| `PATCH` | `/api/orders/:id/status` | Update order status |
| `GET` | `/api/orders/:id/price-estimate` | Calculate price from coords + tariff |
| `GET` | `/api/drivers` | List all drivers with status |
| `GET` | `/api/drivers/nearby?lat=&lng=&radius=` | PostGIS spatial query for nearest free drivers |
| `POST` | `/api/drivers` | Create driver |
| `PATCH` | `/api/drivers/:id` | Update driver profile |
| `PATCH` | `/api/drivers/:id/location` | Update GPS coordinates (from driver app) |
| `PATCH` | `/api/drivers/:id/status` | Set driver online/offline/busy |
| `GET` | `/api/vehicles` | List vehicles |
| `POST` | `/api/vehicles` | Add vehicle |
| `GET` | `/api/tariffs` | List tariffs (filtered by service/class) |
| `GET` | `/api/geozones` | List all geozones with polygons |
| `POST` | `/api/geozones` | Create geozone |
| `GET` | `/api/calls` | Telephony log (with filters) |
| `GET` | `/api/billing/cash` | Kasssa report by operator/period |
| `GET` | `/api/clients` | Client CRM list |
| `GET` | `/api/clients/:phone` | Look up client by phone |
| `WS` | `/ws/monitor` | Real-time dispatch feed: orders, driver locations, status changes |
| `WS` | `/ws/driver/:id` | Driver app feed: incoming order offers, status updates |

### Real-time Architecture
- **WebSockets** (Django Channels / Socket.io / Spring WebSocket) for:
  - Monitor: live order list updates
  - Map: driver GPS position stream
  - Chat: dispatcher ↔ driver messaging
  - Alarms: emergency alerts
- **Redis** as channel layer / pub-sub broker
- **PostGIS** for all spatial queries (`ST_DWithin`, `ST_Contains` for geozone detection)
- **Celery / Cron** for scheduled order triggering (Предварительные)

### Frontend Stack (Next.js)
```
State:        Zustand (multi-tab Monitor state)
Map:          React-Leaflet (OpenStreetMap) or Mapbox GL JS
Real-time:    socket.io-client
Forms:        React Hook Form + Zod
Table:        TanStack Table (Order Journal with 20+ filters)
Auth:         JWT + httpOnly cookies
```

---

## 11. Operational Workflow Summary Table

| Step | Actor | Action | System Result |
|---|---|---|---|
| 1 | Dispatcher | Opens "Новый заказ" (Alt+F1) | Order form opens with embedded map |
| 2 | Dispatcher | Enters phone, name, addresses, class | Distance + price auto-calculated |
| 3 | Dispatcher | Selects distribution method, clicks Ctrl+Enter | Order persists, broadcast to drivers |
| 4 | Driver App | Driver accepts order | Status → Назначен; shown in Текущие заказы |
| 5 | Driver App | Driver arrives at pickup | Status → На месте |
| 6 | Driver App | Trip starts | Status → Везёт; shown on map in real-time |
| 7 | Driver App | Trip ends | Status → Завершён; price finalized |
| 8 | System | Payment processed | Касса updated, driver balance adjusted |
| 9 | Admin | Reviews Журнал заказов | Historical record with all metadata |
| 10 | Admin | Reviews Касса | Net cash flows per operator for period |
